20 questions of db in postgres in leetcode.

 
Agentic Orchestration & MAS: Learn to design Multi-Agent Systems (MAS) where specialized agents (planners, executors, supervisors) collaborate. Master frameworks like LangChain, CrewAI, and LangGraph for disciplined orchestration.

Context Engineering: Replace "prompt engineering" with "context engineering." You must learn how to select, compress, and structure data so agents can operate without "token snowballing" or context window saturation.

Model Context Protocol (MCP) & Universal Standards: Master MCP as the "internal wiki" for agents to connect model reasoning to proprietary datasets like SQL or Slack.

Vector Databases & Advanced RAG: Deepen your knowledge of pgvector, Pinecone, or Milvus to provide agents with a "long-term memory" and factual grounding.

Distributed Resiliency Patterns: As AI-generated code is non-deterministic, you must master Saga patterns, Circuit Breakers, and Event Sourcing to build safety nets that make failures survivable.

Deterministic Verification: Move from writing unit tests to building automated "Verification Layers" that audit agent-generated output for security vulnerabilities and performance bottlenecks.

Cloud-Native & Supercomputing Infrastructure: Understand the hardware-software interplay, specifically managing GPU workloads and high-throughput gRPC/Protobuf APIs that handle the 2x performance demands of agentic systems.